pons. “Initial investigations have indicated that weapons used in the attack were Iranian weapons. Investigations are still ongoing to determine the source of attack. “As the investigations are ongoing, the Kingdom will invite UN and International experts to view the situation on the ground and to participate in the investigations. The Kingdom will take the appropriate measures based on the results of the investigation, to ensure its security and stability. “The Kingdom affirms that is has the capability and resolve to defend its land and people, and to forcefully respond to these aggressions. Oil prices edge up after turbulent week as Saudi Arabia reassures on output(Opens in a new browser tab) The Kingdom of Saudi Arabia expresses its appreciation for the positions taken by the international community that have condemned and denounced this act. The kingdom calls upon the International community to assume its responsibility in condemning those that stand behind this act, and to take a firm and clear position against this reckless behavior that threatens the global economy In an unprecedented act of aggression and sabotage, petroleum facilities in the Kingdom that are vital for global energy supplies were subjected to an attack on Saturday, September 14, 2019, which resulted in suspension of approximately 50% of Saudi Aramco’s production, as noted by the Ministry of Energy’s statement. Vanguard IT was Sunday, May 12 near the port of Fujairah, in the Gulf of Oman, United Arab Emirate, UAE, when four commercial ships were bombed. Two of them, Amjad and Al Marzoqah are tankers owned by Saudi Arabia, the third, A. Michel, an UAE flagged fuel bunker barge and the… May 17, 2019 In "News" Yemen’s Iran-linked Houthi rebels said late Friday that they were halting drone and ballistic missile attacks on Saudi Arabia. The Houthi rebels have claimed recent attacks on major Saudi oil facilities. “We hope Riyadh will respond in a positive way to this initiative. ”And if Saudi Arab